An Act to promote graduate medical education.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 118E of the General Laws is amended by adding at the end thereof, the following
2 new section:-
3 Section 83. MassHealth shall make graduate medical education payments for post-
4 graduate residency and other training in community-based primary care, behavioral health, and
5 other areas of physician or provider shortage in community-based healthcare settings in the
6 Commonwealth. The payments may support community-based training for other health
7 professionals, including but not limited to, family medicine nurse practitioners, dentists, and
8 dental hygienists. Eligible providers for said payments shall include community health centers.
9 MassHealth shall seek to obtain the maximum amount of federal reimbursement for said
10 payments. MassHealth shall promulgate and revise any rules or regulations necessary to
1 of 2

11 implement this provision within 180 days of enactment. MassHealth will prioritize placements at
12 community-based settings and organizations that serve a high public payer mix. MassHealth
13 shall consult with the Massachusetts League of Community Health Centers, Inc. regarding
14 implementation of this section.
